The electoral agency has cleared a total of 12 candidates for the October 14 Kiagu Ward by-election in Meru County.  Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) Returning Officer Pamela Karimi handed the certificates to the aspirants for the seat declared vacant after the death of Eunice Karegi of Governor Alfred Mutua's Maendeleo Chap Chap (MCC).  MCC has fronted Haron Kaburu in a bid to retain the seat, even as UDA associated with Deputy President William Ruto had Senator Mithika Linturi and Central Imenti MP Kirima Nguchine campaigning for its candidate Simon Kiambi.  Also cleared were Samson Magambo (Jubilee), Joseph Mwangi of Democratic Party, Milton Mwenda of Chama Cha Kazi, Patrick Kananda of Chama Cha Uzalendo and Joshua Nabea of Ford Kenya.  Scholastica Mwendwa (Party of Democratic Unity), Douglas Kirimi (Safina), Nathan Gitonga (National Ordinary People Empowerment Union-Nopeu)and Phillip Micheni (Peoples Party of Kenya).  We'll review decisions Chebukati team made, vow IEBC nominees  Why verdict on IEBC might come back to haunt the court  Fate of 27 'endangered' constituencies in limbo as IEBC's time runs out  ODM should not cry foul now over Chebukati and the IEBC  ODM’s attempt to oust Chebukati from IEBC elicits mixed reactions | INSIDE POLITICS WITH BEN KITILI  IEBC launches 2020-2024 Strategic Plan ahead of the 2022 general elections  Uteuzi wa kidato cha kwanza, IEBC imezindua ruwaza na mikakati ya miaka mitano ijayo | MBIU YA KTN By Eric Abuga | 12 hours ago By Standard Reporter | 12 hours ago By Allan Mungai | 19 hours ago By Josphat Thiong’o | 23 hours ago Secret calls that led to removal of Ruto's elite GSU security team